    <a href="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/kolkata/kalam-was-the-only-president-to-fly-supersonic/articleshow/48243943.cms">
    <h4>About A.P.J. Abdul kalam</h4>
    </a>
    <p> A.P.J Abdul kalam, the "Missile Man of India." was born on October 15, 1931, in Ramaeswaram, TamilNadu.
      He served as the 11th President of india and was a reowned scientist, known for his work
      in india's space and missile programs.
    </p>
    </div>
   
    <div>
      <h3>Achievements:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>developed india's first satelite launch vechile(SLV-III)</li>
        <li>Led india's successful nuclear tests in 1998</li>
        <li>wrote books like "Wings of Fire" and "india 2020"</li>
        <li>Recived the Bharat Ratnas, India's highest civilian award</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
